stellaframes-Replacing.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where someone or something is replaced with someone or something else in a specific role or function

stellaframes-BeginningARelationship.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where people start or form a personal relationship with each other

stellaframes-EndingARelationship.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where people end a relationship with each other

stellaframes-JoiningAnOrganization.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where someone starts working as an employee for some organization.

stellaframes-LeavingAnOrganization.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where a person stops working as an employee for an organization.

stellaframes-Getting.definition: The subclass of ChangeOfPossession where a person gets or receives some item.

stellaframes-Giving.definition: The subclass of ChangeOfPossession where a person gives something to someone else.

stellaframes-Buying.definition: The subclass of FinancialTransaction where some entity changes of ownership in exchange for money. Note that the buyer is not necessarily the new owner of the entity.

stellaframes-Selling.definition: The subclass of FinancialTransaction where some entity changes of ownership in exchange for money.

stellaframes-Riot.definition: The subclass of ViolentContest where some group of people engage in a violent disturbance of the public order.

stellaframes-ViolentContest.definition: The subclass of Contest where two parties interact in a hostile manner.

stellaframes-War.definition: The subclass of ViolentContest where there is an armed conflict between different groups of people, two or more countries, etc.

stellaframes-Attacking.definition: The subclass of SocialInteraction where someone or something is assaulted with the intention to cause some harm.

stellaframes-Besieging.definition: The subclass of Attacking where some location is being surrounded and blocked by enemy troops with the aim to cause the surrender of the besieged.

stellaframes-IllegallyTakingSomeoneUnder.definition: The subclass of SocialInteraction where someone illegally takes control over some person or group of persons.

stellaframes-Uprising.definition: The subclass of ViolentContest where humans rise against some authority.

stellaframes-Mutiny.definition: The subclass of Uprising where a group of people rise against some authority, especially used for rebellion at ships or in armies.

stellaframes-PoliticalRevolution.definition: The subclass of Uprising where some government is violently overthrown and replaced by another government.

stellaframes-Shooting.definition: The subclass of Translocation where some object is released from some weapon and is is fired through air with the intention to cause harm or damage.

stellaframes-Invasion.definition: The subclass of Translocation where some country or location is unwelcomely intruded by some armed forces.

stellaframes-Leaving.definition: The subclass of Translocation where someone or something leaves a location.

stellaframes-Arriving.definition: The subclass of Translocation where someone or something arrives at a location.

stellaframes-Dying.definition: The subclass of BiologicalEvent where someone is dying, ultimately resulting in death.

stellaframes-Destroying.definition: The subclass of InternalChange where something gets destroyed.

stellaframes-Repairing.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where some object is modified in such way that it works properly again or can be taken back into itâ€™s intended function.

stellaframes-Damaging.definition: The subclass of InternalChange where something gets damaged.

stellaframes-IntentionalDamaging.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where someone damages something.

stellaframes-Healing.definition: The subclass of BiologicalEvent where a human or animal heals after some injury or illness.

stellaframes-FallingIll.definition: The subclass of BiologicalEvent where a human or animal falls ill or suffers an injury.

stellaframes-Increasing.definition: The subclass of QuantityChange where some physical quantity or value is increased.

stellaframes-Decreasing.definition: The subclass of QuantityChange where some physical quantity or value is decreased.

stellaframes-BeginningContractualAgreeme.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where two parties enter in an agreement described in a contract.

stellaframes-EndingContractualAgreement.definition: Definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where a contract between two parties is broken by one or both of the parties involved.

stellaframes-Transportation.definition: The subclass of Translocation where physical objects and animate beings together change from location and the physical object is not the means of translocation.

stellaframes-Voyage.definition: The subclass of Translocation where a ship travels for a longer period of Time

stellaframes-TransLocation.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where physical objects or animate beings change from location.

stellaframes-BeingLeader.definition: StaticEvent where someone is leader of some group of persons or organization.

stellaframes-BeingInARelationship.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent were people end a relationship with each other.

stellaframes-BeingEmployed.definition: Static event where someone is working in a position and is compensated for her work by some form of payment.

stellaframes-HavingInPossession.definition: Static event where someone holds on to someone or something for a period of Time

stellaframes-Occupation.definition: The subclass of StaticEvent where some group of people, e.g. military have control over some region, e.g. a country or a building.

stellaframes-BeingInConflict.definition: Static event where two people or groups of people are in conflict with each other.

stellaframes-BeingAtAPlace.definition: Static event where some entity is at a location.

stellaframes-BeingDead.definition: The subclass of StaticEvent where some organism is dead.

stellaframes-BeingDestroyed.definition: The subclass of StaticEvent where something is in a destroyed state.

stellaframes-Collaboration.definition: Static event where people work together for some period of Time

stellaframes-HavingAMedicalCondition.definition: The subclass of StaticEvent where some human or animal suffers from a medical condition such as diseases, chronic diseases and disabilities.

stellaframes-BeingDamaged.definition: Static event where some entity is in a damaged state.

stellaframes-HavingInternalState+.definition: Static event where someone or something (which can also be something intangible) is in a better state relatively to an earlier moment.

stellaframes-HavingInternalState-.definition: Static event where someone or something (which can also be something intangible) is in a worse state relatively to an earlier moment.

stellaframes-ChangeOfPossession.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where some entity changes possession. Note that this often but not necessarily implies a change of location of the entity.

stellaframes-FinancialTransaction.definition: The subclass ofChangeOfPossession where some item changes of ownership in exchange for money.

stellaframes-SocialInteraction.definition: The subclass of IntentionalEvent where people interact.

stellaframes-ScalarChange.definition: The subclass of InternalChange where something changes position on a scale.

stellaframes-QuantityChange.definition: The subclass of InternalChange where some quantity is altered.

stellaframes-Miscellaneous.definition: Any event that should be annotated but is not represented in the current event list
